\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. C. barnebiana} B.L. Burtt & P.H. Davis, {\i Kew Bull.}{\b  4}: 103 (1949). Sparsely arachnoid-villous to glabrescent perennial; stems c. 8 cm, simple. Leaves up to 9 × 2 cm, linear-oblanceolate pinnatisect, undulate, with spinose margin. Capitula 15-20 mm in diameter, solitary. Outer involucral bracts 6 mm; inner bracts reddish-purple above and beneath, at least in apical part (sometimes white towards the base). Achenes c. 3 mm; pappus c. 8 mm. •{\i  E. Kriti.} Cr.
\par

