\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. C. vulgaris} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 828, [1231] (1753). Biennial 10-70 cm, subglabrous or with sparsely arachnoid indumentum. Leaves up to 15 cm, linear-oblong to narrowly ovate, more or less spinose-dentate, the lower tapered to a short petiole. Capitula 15-30 mm in diameter, solitary or in terminal groups of 2-3. Outer involucral bracts 10-35(-50) × 4-9 mm, linear-oblong to lanceolate, with spiny margin but scarcely lobed, shorter than or slightly exceeding the inner; inner bracts 12-20 × 1-1·5 mm, straw-coloured. Achenes 3-4 mm; pappus 8 mm. 2n = 20.{\i  Most of Europe, northwards to }62° 30' {\i N. in Finland.} Al Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Gr Hb He Ho Hs Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W, K, E) Si Su Tu.
