\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b longifolia} Nyman, {\i Consp.} 400 (1879) ({\i C. longifolia} Reichenb., non Viv., {\i C. nebrodensis} auct., non Guss. ex DC.): Stem simple or sparingly branched. Leaves linear-oblong, flat, with weakly spiny margin; lateral veins running parallel to the margin and not terminating in teeth. Capitula 20-30 mm in diameter. Outer involucral bracts linear-oblong, somewhat exceeding the inner.{\i  Usually in rather damp grassland. Mainly in the mountain districts of C. Europe, but extending locally to N.E. Spain, N. Appennini, C. Jugoslavia and S. Fennoscandia}.
\par

