\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. C. frigida} Boiss. & Heldr. in Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  1}({\b 6}): 109 (1846) (incl. {\i C. acanthophylla} Hausskn.). Biennial 15-50 cm. Leaves 8-10 × 2-4 cm, deeply pinnatisect with long spines, usually glabrous, rarely tomentose beneath. Capitula 13-20 mm in diameter, in crowded corymbs of 2-6. Outer involucral bracts 35-40 × 20-25 mm, spinose-pinnatisect, much exceeding the inner; inner bracts 12-15 × 1·5 mm, pale yellow or whitish. Florets yellow. •{\i  Mountains of Greece, Albania and W. Jugoslavia.} Al Gr Ju.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. C. fiumensis} Simonkai,{\i  Magyar Bot. Lapok}{\b  6}: 15 (1907). Perennial 12-20 cm, with several stems arising from a short, vertical stock. Leaves 5-12 × 2-3 cm, oblong to oblanceolate, pinnatifid to pinnatisect, narrowed to the base, very crowded. Outer involucral bracts 15-20 × 5-8 mm, spinose-dentate, about equalling the inner; inner bracts 12-15 × 1·5 mm, pale to clear yellow. Florets yellow. •{\i  N.W. Jugoslavia.} Ju.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   A little-known species, which has characters in common with {\b 3}, {\b 6} and {\b 7}, and has been, by different authors, related to each of these.
