\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. C. macrocephala} Moris, {\i Stirp. Sard}. {\b 2}: 5 (1827). Arachnoid-tomentose to subglabrous biennial 15-40 cm; stem simple or sparingly branched. Leaves 7-11 × 2-3 cm, lanceolate, dentate to pinnatifid, undulate, spiny. Capitula terminal. Outer involucral bracts 25-40 × 15-20 mm; inner bracts 13-17 × 1·5-2 mm, white above (rarely purple at apex), purplish beneath. Achenes c. 4 mm; pappus c. 8 mm. •{\i  C. Mediterranean region.} Co It Sa Si.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b macrocephala}: Capitula 1-4, 25-30 mm in diameter. Outer involucral bracts distinctly exceeding the inner. 2n = 20. {\i Corse, Sardegna}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b nebrodensis} (Guss. ex DC.) D. A. Webb,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  68}: 279 (1974) ({\i C. nebrodensis} Guss. ex DC.): Capitula usually more than 4, c. 18 mm in diameter. Outer involucral bracts scarcely exceeding the inner. {\i Italy, Sicilia, ?Corse}.
\par

